  "title": "Snr IT Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Summary</strong><br />We are looking for an IT engineer to join the team in supporting Windows environment and network infrastructure.<br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Provide Network administration, support and monitoring on Switches, Routers, Firewalls</li><li>Provide System Administration on Windows, Linux Servers inclusive of Virtualization technologies</li><li>Maintain Active Directory, LDAP, LAN/WAN, Storage and relevant server protocols</li><li>Maintain System Inventory and update documentation and technical report</li><li>Provide End User Support</li><li>Involve in BCM exercise</li><li>Any other task assigned by IT Manager</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Possess a Diploma or Degree in IT or equivalent</li><li>Sound technical knowledge in Cisco/Fortinet and Networking platforms</li><li>Sound technical knowledge in Wintel/Linux operating systems</li><li>Sound technical knowledge in resolving various computer hardware and configuration issues</li><li>Minimum 2 year working experience in the role</li><li>Able to work independently as well as in a team & ability to thrive in a fast paced and dynamic environment</li><li>Technical knowledge and experience in cloud technologies & multiple real time concurrent systems an additional advantage</li><li>Comfortable with being “on call” for any emergencies after work hours and on weekends</li><li>Resourceful and knowledgeable of IT is an added advantage</li></ul>",
